<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_1">Sensors indicate a small Lanius cruiser in the process of salvaging another small Lanius ship. Before you have a chance to wonder what caused them to turn on each other, the survivor notices you and moves in to attack. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_10">You have stumbled across a mining expedition - unfortunately, the miners are the Lanius, and they've chosen your ship as their target! [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_2">Shortly after your arrival, a Lanius ship jumps near the beacon. It begins to move slowly toward you. You open wide band communication channels, attempting to make contact. However, it either ignores you or is unable to receive the messages. As they get closer you issue the order to charge weapons and find they do the same. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_3">You receive a message on a wide band frequency, originating from an approaching Lanius ship. It appears not to be directed at you, but your translator does its best all the same: "... metallic opportunity... acquisition... by force..." Looks like you're in for a fight. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_4">A military Lanius vessel stops repurposing an abandoned satellite as soon as you jump in. It blocks all hails and powers its weapons. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_5">The beacon is surrounded by many tiny Lanius craft, surely only capable of holding one occupant. Perhaps they are some kind of forward scout searching for 'metallic opportunities'? As you consider this, a much larger Lanius vessel moves in to engage you, and the scout ships scatter in all directions. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_6">You arrive to see a well-armed Lanius craft preparing to salvage a badly damaged Rebel patrol ship. Noticing your arrival, the Lanius greedily moves in to intercept its second target of the day. [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_7">As you arrive in the system, your proximity alarm begins screaming: there is a Lanius ship right on top of you! Before you have a chance to hail, they open fire! [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_8">As you are getting your bearings, another ship suddenly arrives at the beacon - it's the Lanius, and they've marked your ship for salvage! [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_FIGHT_TEXT_9">At first everything seems quiet, then your scanners pick up a ship approaching at high speed - the Lanius have detected your arrival and are powering up their weapons! [ Lanius Ship Fight Default Lanius Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.2, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_PIRATE_FIGHT_TEXT_1">A pirate ship appears to be threatening a small refugee ship near the beacon. Upon seeing you jump in, it turns to approach. The civilian wastes no time and jumps away, but that appears only to harden the pirate's resolve. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_PIRATE_FIGHT_TEXT_2">An upgraded pirate ship sits among the remains of a number of Lanius ships. It hails you, "These punks think they can jus' waltz in here into our sector? Obnoxious, right? Well, I'Med. sure you know the routine, let's do this." [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_PIRATE_FIGHT_TEXT_3">Debris from a number of battleships are scattered around the beacon. As you approach the area a pirate ship thrusts itself through the hulks to attack. It must be using the metal to lure the Lanius into a trap. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_PIRATE_FIGHT_TEXT_4">The pirate ship patroling this sector has been busy. The debris of several Rebel scouts and at least one civilian ship litter the area. "Welcome, welcome, there's room for one more!" The over-confident pirate hails you as he charges his weapons and moves in to attack. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_PIRATE_FIGHT_TEXT_5">The pirate sees you before you see him... prepare for a fight! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_1">You arrive to see a number of Rebel ships attempting to dissuade Lanius scavenger ships from "acquiring" their forward station. A passing Rebel patrol ship spots you and moves in to intercept. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_2">A Rebel scout patrols near the beacon. "Hah! I knew you would try to sneak through this sector as soon as I heard it had become treacherous. Surrender!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_3">You intercept discussions between a Rebel patrol and a human mining colony, "... we realize you're scared but all reports indicate the metal bastards target abandoned settlements only. If we relocated our fleets based on every request from backwater... wait, what's that..." Before you can react, the channel is cut and the Rebel ship moves in to attack. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_4">You arrive at the beacon and notice a small Rebel ship chasing Lanius scavengers away from a wrecked Rebel battleship. As soon as the Rebel notices you and moves in to attack, the Lanius ships return to their prey like flies on garbage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_5">A Rebel messages you. "Who would have thought the most wanted ship in the quadrant would just happen by my station? Prepare to meet your maker." [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_LANIUS_REBEL_FIGHT_TEXT_6">Your arrival coincides almost exactly with that of a Rebel ship. It's hard to know who is more surprised, but there is no option but to fight. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_LANIUS_1">This sector has been largely abandoned since a series of battles decimated the local population. An unusual alien race is reportedly scavenging in the area. You'd best be on guard. [ 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 5-6 Hostile, 1-2 Hostile Envs, 1-2 Boarder, 2-4 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_LANIUS_2">This sector was the site of many major battles between the Federation and Rebel fleets. Strangely, there's very little evidence of those battles remaining... [ 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 5-6 Hostile, 1-2 Hostile Envs, 1-2 Boarder, 2-4 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_LANIUS_3">There have been a number of reports of advanced ships salvaging the wrecks and abandoned mining facilities in this sector. Could it be that the Lanius have resurfaced? [ 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 5-6 Hostile, 1-2 Hostile Envs, 1-2 Boarder, 2-4 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_LANIUS_4">The war tore through this civilian sector, and just recently even the few life signs that remained have begun blinking out. Rumours suggest the Lanius are responsible. [ 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 5-6 Hostile, 1-2 Hostile Envs, 1-2 Boarder, 2-4 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

