<text name="event_MERCENARY_c4_choice">You have no need of his services. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_1_c1_choice">Agree to rescue the store. [ Space Dock Rescue Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_2_c1_choice">Accept. [ Pirate Ship Fight Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 3-4, Med. Scrap & Weapon ]; Kill Reward: Low Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_START_c1_choice">Listen to their offer. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_START_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c1_choice">Dock with the station and investigate. [ MDrones | Crew Gain, 3-4 Human Boarders | Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss), avoid w/Lvl 2+ Medbay ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c3_choice">(Anti-Personnel Missle) Use an Anti-Personnel Missle to investigate. [ x2 -1 Missle | -1 Missle, Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c1_choice">Accept the paltry payment.</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c2_choice">Refuse and keep the Missle parts. [ Nothing Happens | 40-55 Scrap offer ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_c1_choice">Accept the new offer.</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Mind Control) Convince him that he's being 'unfair'. [ 40-55 Scrap offer ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c4_choice">(Weapons) Remain silent but power up your weapons. [ +55-70 Scrap, +2-5 Fuel, -5 Drones ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_1_c1_choice">Take the cargo and head to its original destination in search of a reward. [ Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_1_c2_choice">Take the cargo for yourself. [ Weapon | High Standard | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c1_choice">Promise to deliver the cargo and ask if any would be interested in joining your crew. [ Crew Gain, Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c2_choice">Take the cargo but drop them off at a nearby station. [ Weapon | High Standard | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Beam the cargo aboard and leave them to their fate. [ Weapon | High Standard | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_3_text">After a quick scan, you find a ship being chased by a pirate. This must be the missing delivery ship! You move in to rescue them. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_c1_choice">Yes. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_c2_choice">No. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_LIST_1_c1_text">"Great! I uploaded their location to your star map. I'Med. running out of options, so I have no choice but to trust you'll do what you have agreed to do." [ +5 Drones, Merchant Delivery Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_LIST_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_LIST_2_c1_text">"At least you're confident, for what little that's worth. Here is their last known location." [ Merchant Investigate Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | LWeap | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c1_text">You power up your weapons and engage the pirate ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | LWeap | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c3_choice">(Improved Weapons) Fire a warning shot from your strongest weapon. [ Straight to Double | Same as 'Aid the civilian ship' ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c1_choice">Attack the pirate. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: Low Resources; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-4, Med. Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c3_choice">(Fire Beam) Show the pirate how to intimidate settlers: burn their crops! [ High Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c4_choice">(Fire Bomb) Show the pirate how to intimidate settlers: start fires in their crude dwellings. [ High Scrap & Missle Schematic, -1 Missle ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_CONTINUE_c1_choice">Agree to capture the ship. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_CONTINUE_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c1_choice">Offer your services. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Offer to board their ship. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c4_choice">(Bio Beam) Offer to 'remove' their crew. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c5_choice">(Fire Bomb) Offer to burn the crew out. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_text">You find the ship that you were asked to capture intact. You're not sure why, but they stressed that it's of great importance that you kill the crew WITHOUT destroying the ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: -15 Hull; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_c1_choice">Accept. [ LFuel, Escort Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_ARRIVE_1_text">You escort the ship to the requested beacon. Much to your dismay you are ambushed by a Rebel ship. You walked right into their trap! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c1_choice">Leave before they notice you. [ Nothing Happens | Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c2_choice">(Missile Weapon) Bombard their key structures. [ -1 Missle, Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c3_choice">(2 Fire Bombs) Teleport fire bombs into key structures. [ -2 Missle, High Resources, Engi Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_START_c1_choice">Pledge to do what you can. [ MScrap, Mantis War Camp Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_START_c2_choice">Apologize and decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_STORE_RESCUE_c1_choice">Engage the Rebel and rescue the space dock. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap; Crew Kill Reward: MScrap; Double Reward: [ +5 Hull, Store ] ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_STORE_RESCUE_c2_choice">Avoid a fight. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_c1_choice">Aid the Federation ship. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | Med. Standard | Low Standard, Crew Gain, BOs for more ] ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_c1_text">You power up your weapons and engage the Rebel ship. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | Med. Standard | Low Standard, Crew Gain, BOs for more ] ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_c2_choice">Use this chance to escape. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c1_choice">Quickly try to rescue the crew. [ Crew Gain, Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c2_choice">(Nano Med-bot Dispersal) Pump their ship with Nano Med-bots to aid in the rescue. [ Crew Gain w/Shield skill, High Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Lock on to all remaining life signatures and beam them onto your ship. [ Crew Gain w/Combat skill, MScrap, Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c4_choice">(Healing Burst) Use a healing bomb to keep them alive. [ -1 Missle, Crew Gain w/Engines skill, MScrap, Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c1_choice">Scrap it. [ HScrap | Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c3_choice">(Crystal Crew) Reactivate it. [ +1 Fuel, Jump to Crystal Sector ]</text>
<text name="event_START_BEACON_text">Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you! [ 2-3 Stores, 2-3 Items, 2-4 Neutral, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 0-8 Nebula, 0-2 Quests ]</text>
<text name="event_START_GAME_text">The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up! [ 1-2 Stores, 1 Item, 2-4 Neutral, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 0-4 Nebula, 1 Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c1_choice">Dock with the station and investigate. [ MDrones | Crew Gain, 3-4 Human Boarders | Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss), avoid w/Lvl 2+ Medbay ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c3_choice">(Anti-Personnel Missle) Use an Anti-Personnel Missle to investigate. [ x2 -1 Missle | -1 Missle, Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c4_choice">(Life Scanner) Run advanced life scans. [ Nothing | Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_STORE_RESCUE_c1_choice">See if you can assist them. [ Space Dock Rescue Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_STORE_RESCUE_c2_choice">Ignore their pleas. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_1_c1_choice">Invite him to join your crew. [ Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_1_c2_choice">Take him home to his family on a nearby planet in this system. [ HScrap | MScrap | +10 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c1_choice">Bring him back to your ship in hopes of finding some help for him. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) | Crew Gain | -5 Hull | Crew Gain w/Lvl2 CB/MB) ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c2_choice">Leave the madman to his ravings, he's not worth the risk. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c3_choice">(Improved Medbay) Bring him to your medbay. [ Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c4_choice">(Advanced Medbay) Bring him to your medbay. [ Crew Gain w/Max Skills ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c5_choice">(Slug Crew) "Sir, allow me to assess his mental state." [ HumanCrew Gain | Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_BEACON_c1_choice">Go down to the surface to investigate. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_BEACON_c2_choice">Ignore the signal. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c1_choice">Participate in their study. [ x2 LScrap | 2 Boarders, Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: Low Resources, Missle ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c3_choice">(Advanced Medbay) Give them your medical records. [ Missle, Low Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c4_choice">(Damaged Stasis Pod) Ask if they can fix this. [ Crystal Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_LIST_3_text">As soon as you dock, pirates burst on board and a hostile ship appears on the radar. You hear the Zoltans yell in the distance, "We're being held hostage!" [ 2 Boarders, Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: Low Resources, Missle ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_escape_text">You pick up more chatter from the enemy ship, "You know what... Forget this. Prepare for retreat!" Looks like they're preparing to make a hasty get away! [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 5s, Mantis Chase Quest ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_gotaway_c1_choice">After them! [ Mantis Quest Chase ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_gotaway_c2_choice">Forget it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_escape_text">They appear to be trying to get away again. You doubt they'll forget to mask their jump signature this time. [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard Weapon; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard Weapon; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 2-2, HScrapWeap; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 6-6, 12s, High Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_surrender_c1_choice">Let them live. [ HScrapWeap ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_surrender_c2_choice">Finish them off. [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard Weapon; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard Weapon; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 6-6, 12s, High Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_1">You arrive at the beacon and immediately detect a pirate ship. It seems this distress beacon was a trap! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_2">"Haha! I knew someone would fall into our dastardly trap!" It appears this distress beacon was nothing but a decoy for a pirate ambush. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_3">Your cockpit lights up with warning signals. You are being targeted by a nearby ship. The distress call was a lure to attract unwitting ships into weapons range. You prepare for a fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_4">As soon as you arrive at the distress signal, shots are fired toward your ship. A trap! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>

<!-- data/events_boss.xml -->
<text name="event_LAST_STAND_START_c1_c1_text">Tully responds, "It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck." [ 1 Store, 3 Repair, 6 Hostile, 7-10 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_1">You arrive in the middle of a raging battle. Both sides are taking heavy losses. A small squadron flies past and a fighter breaks off, moving toward your position. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_2">Two fleets fight nearby. You try to skirt around the edges of the battle and keep out of weapons range, but a Rebel scout spots you and moves in. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_3">It's hard to tell who is winning the nearby battle. Before you have a chance to figure it out, a fighter moves in to attack. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_4">The sheer scale of the destruction in the distance is almost breath-taking. Unfortunately, your position as an independent observer doesn't last for long! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_5">The destruction in the distance is almost awe-inspiring. However you're dragged back to reality as Sensors indicate you are under attack. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_6">You don't have any time to worry about the battle in the distance. The fight is coming to you really quickly! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_1">Although you were expecting the Rebels, you never imagined their fleet could have grown so fast. You scanners can hardly register them all before a fighter stationed nearby moves in to attack. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_2">This system is flooded with Rebel warships. Luckily your ship's signature is disguised as a civilian transport. Most heavy vessels ignore you but a small fighter is approaching with weapons hot! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_3">You arrive to find a Rebel battalion encircling a nearby planet, launching landing parties. A small scout moves toward your position. Prepare for a fight! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_4">As soon as you arrive you find yourself in the debris of a fierce battle. However, only Rebel warships remain and you find yourself immediately under attack. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_5">Shots fly by and your computer registers multiple weapon locks as soon as you arrive. Evasive action! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_6">What was once a great series of space stations is now nothing but a small ring of debris around the nearby moon. There's no time to mourn the dead; an enemy approaches! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_7">The Federation seems to have put up a good fight. A number of Rebel ships lie broken or wounded. However their overwhelming numbers force the remaining Federation forces to retreat. Hopefully you can get away in time as well. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_1">Although this sector is still under Federation control, a small scout has slipped by the fleet. You move in to engage. [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_2">Long range scanners show this system is empty of any capital ships. Clearly it is not of strategic value. Wait... FTL signatures show a Rebel scout just jumped nearby! [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_3">Sensors indicate that the Rebels are setting up a forward Jump Beacon behind the nearby planet's moon. More importantly, a number of ships are passing by; prepare for a fight! [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_4">Federation ships are scarce in this region of space despite a number of civilian space stations. You see a small bomber squadron engaged with some Federation scouts and quickly move in to assist. [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_5">As soon as you arrive at the beacon, a Rebel scout turns to engage. Power up the weapons! [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_6">You scan the area, finding signatures for only a small trade vessel. However, as it approaches you see the silhouette of a Rebel scout! You run the scanners again and discover their registration is fake. You move in to attack. [ Rebel/Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_1">Shots fly by your port windows followed by a Rebel scout in pursuit of a damaged cruiser. Should we move in to engage? [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | Med. Resources ]; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 4-8 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_2">There seems to be a small Federation colony under attack by a Rebel forward scout. Will you protect them? [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | Med. Resources ]; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 4-8 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_3">A number of large transports are being pursued by a Rebel bombing squadron. One bomber has managed to slip through the defensive fire, and is poised to wreak havoc among the enormous yet vulnerable transports. There's time for you to advance and take it out! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | Med. Resources ]; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 4-8 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_4">A battle rages nearby between small fighters; apparently fighting over a space station. The Federation appears to be losing ships fast. Shall we assist them? [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | Med. Resources ]; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 4-8 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_5">A civilian ship is broadcasting a request for assistance on a secure Federation channel. They are being harassed by Rebel scouts. Will you respond? [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | Med. Resources ]; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 4-8 ]</text>

<!-- data/events_crystal.xml -->
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_AUTO_text">The Rebels must have sent their automated scouts to find you. One jumps in and immediately moves to attack. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c1_choice">Attempt to break through with the weapons you have. [ x2 Nothing Happens | [ Low Resources, Crystal Weapon | Low Resources, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, Low Resources or BOs ] ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c2_choice">(Breach Missiles) Use a Breach Missile. [ -1 Missle, [ Low Resources, Crystal Weapon | Low Resources, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, Low Resources or BOs ] ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c3_choice">(Crystal crewmember) Have your Crystalline Being recalibrate your weapons. [ Low  Resources, Crystal Weapon | Low  Resources, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ -1 Crew (Clone Bay Revive) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, Low  Resources or BOs ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c1_choice">Pull out now! [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c2_choice">Detonate your entire fuel reserves to escape with your crew and the cargo. [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, Low Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c3_choice">(Improved Teleporter) Beam your crewmember back on board. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c4_choice">(Advanced Engines) Rescue your crewmember and the cargo. [ Weapon, Low Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_choice">Yes. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_c1_choice">Try to answer his questions. [ +6 Hull | Random Resources | Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_c2_choice">"I don't have time for this." [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c2_choice">No. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c3_choice">(Crystal Crew) Have your crew speak to them. [ Random Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_LIST_1_text">You speak at length about nothing particularly interesting. "Wow, thanks. Oh look, another alien ship! I wonder if they're as nice as you." Seeing the Rebel decals you doubt they're friendly. They spot you and move in to attack, while the Crystalline civilian jumps away. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CONVOY_text">A large convoy of lumbering civilian ships appears to be passing through this region. You show no hostile intentions, but they are taking no chances, immediately sending their escort to attack! [ Cry Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0, 3-4, [ Low Scrap & Fuel, +8 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_c1_choice">Save the Federation ship. [ Cry Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ Random Resources | Low Standard, Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_c2_choice">Prepare to leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c1_choice">Offer supplies. [ -1-3 Fuel, -15-25 Scrap, Map ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c2_choice">Attack the traitors. [ Fed Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c3_choice">Leave them be. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_choice">Send a crewmember to help. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c1_choice">Leave your crewmember behind. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss), Med. Scrap & Fuel (High Scrap & Fuel if Waited) ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c2_choice">Pull your guy out. [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c3_choice">Wait. [ Fleet Advance, [ Crystal Heavy 2, HAugment if wait twice ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c1_choice">Allow them to run tests on a crewmember. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), Low Scrap & Weapon | Med. Resources | Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c2_choice">Refuse. [ x2 Nothing Happens | Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c3_choice">(Rock crewmember) Send your Rockman crew. [ Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c4_choice">(Backup DNA Bank) Send your crew's data. [ Med. Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUNTER_text">Crystal shards fly past your ship as soon as you jump. You scan to find the assailant and discover a Crystalline ship carrying a number of humans in its cargo bay. It must be hunting the intruding ships! [ Cry Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, HumanCrew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_MANTIS_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the Mantis. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ x2 Nothing Happens | x2 Random Resources | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_MANTIS_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_PIRATE_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the pirate. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ x2 Nothing Happens | x2 Random Resources | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_PIRATE_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_text">As soon as you arrive, a Rebel ship jumps in after you; they must be really hot on your tail. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the Rebel. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ x2 Nothing Happens | x2 Random Resources | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Attack the Crystalline ship. [ Fleet Advance, Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c3_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL2_c1_choice">Engage the Rebel ship. [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL2_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c1_choice">Give them your flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c2_choice">Accept the scrap but give them false flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet Delay | 1-2 Crystal Borders, Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c3_choice">(Distraction Buoy) Accept the scrap but give them falsified flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet Delay ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c4_choice">Refuse. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_choice">Offer 35 scrap. [ Crystal Crew Gain or [ Crystal Bomb | Crystal Burst 2 ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_c1_choice">Accept. [ Crystal Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_c2_choice">Request another payment. [ Crystal Bomb | Crystal Burst 2 ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c2_choice">Turn him down. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SHIP_SURRENDER_7_c1_choice">Yes. [ Crystal Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SHIP_SURRENDER_7_c2_choice">No. [ Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_START_BEACON_CRYSTAL_c1_text">"You have done as you promised and so shall I. The coordinates of my old ship have been forwarded to your navigation system." [ 2-3 Stores, 2 Items, 2 Empty, 6-10 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 12 Neutral ] [ Crystal Unlock Quest ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_1">You arrive near a fleet of crystal ships, civilian or mercantile from the looks of them. You pause to scan one but they react immediately and send an escort to fight you off. Prepare to engage! [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_2">You arrive at the Beacon and are immediately greeted by an automatic message or warning of some kind. The translator can't seem to discern its purpose but after a few short moments an alarm goes off and a hostile ship jumps in! [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_3">You receive a message, "Hah. It looks like another worthless alien-filled craft. Prepare to meet your maker!" Weapon locks detected. [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_4">A Crystalline ship messages you, "I've heard tales that our isolation has finally ended. As a warrior I must demand to test my skills against you!" Before you can respond they move in to attack. [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_5">You arrive in a busy sector. At first no one pays any mind to your alien ship but soon you're registering a number of scan signatures. You get the feeling you're not wanted here just seconds before registering enemy weapon locks! [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_6">You jump next to a node busy with traffic, but before long all nearby ships notice you and keep their distance, uncertain of your allegiance. After an awkward standoff, a military ship breaks away from the rest and charges you. [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_7">A barrage of rasps and clicks is broadcast over the comm; the universal translator understands little, but the words 'aliens', 'allowed' and 'no' come through quite clearly. You'll have to prove your right to be here in combat! [ Cry Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.6, 3-4 [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ] ]</text>

<!-- data/events_engi.xml -->
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c1_choice">Board the station. [ Nothing Happens | More... ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c2_choice">Ignore it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c3_choice">(Improved Sensors) Run another scan. [ Engi Crew Gain, LScrap | Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c4_choice">(Long Ranged Scanners) Run another scan. [ Engi Crew Gain, LScrap | Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c1_choice">Save the Engi! [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), LScrap, Engi Crew Gain | LScrap, Engi Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c2_choice">Save the Missle schematic. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), LScrap | Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c3_choice">Save yourselves! [ LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_SCAN_c1_choice">Save the Engi! [ Engi Crew Gain, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_SCAN_c2_choice">Save the Missle Schematic! [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_text">The distress signal originates from a small Engi ship under attack by a rebel fighter - but when the Rebels see Federation markings they turn to attack! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: Trade offers ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c1_choice">Give them 25 scrap. [ Nothing Happens | HealBomb | Missle ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c2_choice">Give them 40 scrap, 2 missiles and 2 fuel. [ MedBot Augment ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c3_choice">Give them nothing. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_FLEET_DELAY_c1_choice">Booby trap the cache. [ -2 Missle, Fleet Delay x2 ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_FLEET_DELAY_c2_choice">Secure the cache. [ Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_PIRATE_FIGHT_text">There must have been rich pickings for pirates around here up until war broke out. The pirate you encounter here looks worn down, but hungry. You'll have to fight! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_REBEL_FIGHT_text">The rebel fighter here would seem to suggest elements of the rebel fleet are already making incursions on Engi space. You move to engage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c1_choice">Attempt to help the ships by prying them apart. [ Engi Ship Fight with no rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c2_choice">Ignore the damaged vessels. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c3_choice">(Engi Crew) Have your Engi crewmember hail the vessel and assess the damage. [ Med. Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Explain that you're friendly. [ Nothing Happens | Random Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SURRENDER_c2_choice">Accept their offer of surrender. [ Random Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_c1_choice">Respond to the call and move in to assist. [ Engi w/Mantis Crew Ship Fight Default Rewards, 1-2 Boarders | Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Nothing Happens | MFuel | Engi Crew Gain, Low Standard | [ Option of Fuel/Weapon/Missle/Engi Blue Option ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_c2_choice">Keep your distance. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_LIST_1_text">You receive another message from the ship, this time with a Mantis at the comm-log. "Foolish meatsacks," he yells. Sensors indicate the ship is moving in to attack and boarders teleport from the station. [ Engi w/Mantis crew Ship Fight Default Rewards 1-2 Mantis Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_LIST_2_text">You approach to find a Mantis ship assaulting a small Engi space station. You prepare for a fight! [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Double Reward: [ Nothing Happens | MFuel | Engi Crew Gain, Low Standard | [ Option of Fuel/Weapon/Missle/Engi Blue Option ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_UNLOCK_3_text">You have finally caught up with the ships you've been hunting. A hangar-sized cargo ship is being escorted by a number of Mantis ships. As you reconsider the assault, a squadron of Engi ships with pirate emblems jump in and assist you. You prepare to fight the Mantis but scans indicate they are manned by Rebels! [ Mantis w/Human crew Ship Fight Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: +20 Hull, High Standard, Titanium System Casing ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c1_choice">Hold on! Let us try to purge the system code! [ Engi Ship Fight w/Shields@0 + Engines@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c2_choice">Attack the Engi vessel! [ Engi Ship Fight Kill Reward:Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Isolate and quarantine the virus. [ Low Standard, Missle Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c4_choice">(Improved Hacking) Reprogram the virus. [ +15 Hull, Reactor+1, Missle Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c5_choice">(Advanced Hacking) Reprogram the virus. [ +30 Hull, Reactor+1, Missle Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c6_choice">(Lanius Crew) Your Lanius crewmember gestures frantically. [ MScrap, Missle Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c7_choice">(Engi Crew) Have your Engi crewmember negotiate with the Engi ship. [ Engi Crew Loss, Engi Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: Engi Crew Gain w/Max Skills ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_ENGI_STATION_3_c1_choice">Request fuel. [ High Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_ENGI_STATION_3_c2_choice">Request weapon. [ Low Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_ENGI_STATION_3_c3_choice">Request Missle. [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_ENGI_STATION_3_c4_choice">(Engi Crew) Threat unresolved. Current mission imperative: Protocol 52.34. [ +10 Hull, Low Scrap & Weapon, Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="text_ENGI_MANTIS_FIGHT_1">A mixed radar signal turns out to be a Mantis attack ship scavenging the remains of an Engi carrier. They turn and fight. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ENGI_MANTIS_FIGHT_2">You come across a Mantis raider taking pot shots at a defenceless Engi supply station. Discovering its weapons aren't much of a match for the station's armour, it turns on your ship. Battle stations! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ENGI_MANTIS_FIGHT_3">The area looks clear, and you prepare to jump off, but a Mantis scout jumps in behind you! They're as surprised as you are, but their weapons are already online. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ENGI_MANTIS_FIGHT_4">You find a Mantis ship harrying a small squad of Engi. They make it to the node and jump off, leaving you toe to toe with their pursuer! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ENGI_1">You have arrived in Engi space. The Mantis have been threatening the Engi core worlds, but you should be able to stock up for your journey. [ 2-3 Stores, 2 Items, 1-2 Empty, 3 Engi-Items, 1-3 Distress, 1 Quest, 4-6 Neutral, 5-7 Hostile ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ENGI_2">You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help. [ 2-3 Stores, 2 Items, 1-2 Empty, 3 Engi-Items, 1-3 Distress, 1 Quest, 4-6 Neutral, 5-7 Hostile ]</text>

<!-- data/events_fuel.xml -->
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_c1_choice">Graciously accept their offer. [ 2-6 Fuel | Various Fuel Trades | 2-3 Human Boarders, Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_c2_choice">Request that they keep their distance. [ 1-4 Fuel | Nothing Happens | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_c3_choice">(Advanced Sensors) Run a detailed scan with your sensors before responding. [ 3-7 Fuel | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Blue Option Cloak to avoid) ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_c4_choice">(Long-Ranged Scanners) Run a detailed scan before responding. [ 3-7 Fuel | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Blue Option Cloak to avoid ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_ACCEPT_LIST_2_c1_choice">Gladly trade. [ Expensive Fuel Offers ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_ACCEPT_LIST_2_c2_choice">Respectfully decline. [ Cheaper Fuel Offers | Expensive Fuel Offers | Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_ACCEPT_LIST_3_text">As their ship pulls up next to yours, their captain continues, "Yes, we'll certainly help... Help to relieve you of that nice ship!" Sensors detect a hidden teleporter has been activated. We've been boarded! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards, 2-3 Human Boarders, Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_ACCEPT_LIST_4_text">As they approach, you detect their weapons powering up. It seems their intentions are hostile! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_DECLINE_LIST_3_text">They reply,"Keep our distance? Let's see if you can stop us!" They power up their weapons and advance. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_SCAN_LIST_2_c1_choice">Power up weapons and prepare for a fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_APPROACH_SCAN_LIST_2_c2_choice">(Cloaking) Cloak and get out of scanning range before they have a chance to lock on. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_EXPLORE_c1_choice">Explore the nearby area. [ Fuel for Scrap Trades | Nothing Happens | Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel | [ Nothing Happens | HFuel | Med. Scrap & Missles | Med. Scrap & Drones | -5 Hull | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ] ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_EXPLORE_c2_choice">Stay near the beacon. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_EXPLORE_LIST_4_text">You wander within scanning range of a small Rebel automated scout! [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel, Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ENGI_DUBIOUS_c1_choice">Hail them. [ Nothing Happens | 2-6 Fuel | Engi Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel, Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel | Fuel Trade Offer ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ENGI_DUBIOUS_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ENGI_DUBIOUS_c3_choice">(Hull Repair Missle) Offer to help repair their hull. [ -1 Missle, +4-6 Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ENGI_DUBIOUS_LIST_2_text">The Engi fail to respond, but move to intercept. You detect abnormal electromagnetic signals aboard the ship - someone has reprogrammed them to fight! [ Engi Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_CURIOUS_c1_choice">Attack. [ Rock Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel, Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_CURIOUS_c1_text">The Rock people are not renowned for their generosity. If it's fuel you need, it's fuel you must take! [ Rock Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_CURIOUS_c2_choice">Wait and see. [ 3-8 Fuel | Rock Ship Fight w/Engines@1; Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_CURIOUS_LIST_2_text">The Rock ship circles yours, running scans on your systems. Your worst fears are confirmed when they identify your engines and teleport a bomb straight onto it! Combat ready! [ Rock Ship Fight w/Engines@1; Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_WRECK_c1_choice">Send an away team. [ Med. Scrap & Missles | x2 MFuel | [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) or -25-40 scrap ] ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_WRECK_c2_choice">Let it drift by. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_WRECK_c3_choice">(Life Scanner) Run additional scans. [ MFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_WRECK_LIST_4_c1_choice">Pay. [ -25-40 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_OFF_ROCK_WRECK_LIST_4_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_REBEL_WARNING_text">A ship responding to your distress moves in. Unfortunately it turns out to be an automated Rebel scout. It immediately reverses thrust after scanning your ship. [ Auto Ship Fight; Kill Reward: Low Standard; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 40s, 22-22, Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_CHUCKLE_c1_choice">Pay 15 scrap for 5 fuel. [ 5 Fuel for 15 Scrap | 5 Fuel for 15 Scrap, -20-35 Scrap, -2-4 Missle ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_CHUCKLE_c2_choice">Ignore the offer. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_CHUCKLE_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Have your Slug make the purchase. [ 5 Fuel for 15 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_OVERPRICED_c1_choice">Buy 5 fuel for 50 scrap. [ 5 Fuel for 50 scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_OVERPRICED_c2_choice">Buy 10 fuel for 95 scrap. (BEST DEAL!) [ 10 Fuel for 95 scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_OVERPRICED_c3_choice">Negotiate. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel, Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_ON_SLUG_OVERPRICED_c3_text">You offer a more reasonable price but the Slugman is outraged! He moves in to attack! [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_SELLER_DISTRESS_c1_choice">Request emergency fuel reserves. [ LFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_SELLER_DISTRESS_c4_choice">Attack the automated ship. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_TRADER_DISTRESS_c2_choice">Respectfully decline. [ Cheaper Fuel Offers | Expensive Fuel Offers | Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_TRADER_PT2_1_c2_choice">Decline again. [ Nothing Happens | +1-6 Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_FUEL_TRADER_PT2_2_c2_choice">Decline again. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_DAMAGED_c2_choice">(Engi Crew) Negotiate a better trade. [ 6 Fuel for 10 Scrap Offer ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_DAMAGED_c2_c2_choice">Refuse it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_DAMAGED_c3_choice">Refuse their offer. [ Nothing Happens | 6 Fuel for 10 Scrap Offer ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_DAMAGED_c4_choice">The helpless refugees make easy targets. Attack them. [ Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_PIRATE_c1_choice">Offer some missiles for fuel. [ 5-7 Fuel for 1 Missile | 5-7 Fuel for 1 Missile, Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_PIRATE_c2_choice">Refuse their offer. [ LFuel | x2 Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_PIRATE_ACCEPT_2_text">Having traded supplies, the ship suddenly powers up and attacks - it's a pirate ship! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NO_FUEL_REFUGEE_PIRATE_REJECT_3_text">Taking your reluctance as weakness, the refugee ship suddenly bristles with weapons - it's a pirate ship, and it believes it's found easy prey! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_MANTIS_ATTACK_1">A Mantis ship hails you, "Looks like we found the poor fools that need some help. Come brothers, let's 'help' them!" They move in to attack. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_MANTIS_ATTACK_2">Before long a ship jumps nearby, no doubt responding to your beacon. However any relief you felt disappears as soon as you recognize that the ship is of Mantis design. Prepare for a fight. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_MANTIS_ATTACK_3">You detect a Mantis ship approaching and hack into their comm channel and hear, "...hope they put up more of a fight than the last Federation ship. This has been a disappointing day so far." Looks like they're not here to help. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_MANTIS_ATTACK_4">A Mantis ship jump nearby. Sensors detect weapon locks and all hope of avoiding a fight fades away. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_REBEL_ATTACK_1">A Rebel ship hails you, "Hello citizen. We are responding to your distress call and can assist... Wait a second... You're that ship! Prepare to die!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_REBEL_ATTACK_2">A Rebel ship jumps nearby, "I wasn't looking forward to patrolling this boring sector but here you are, the most wanted ship in the area, just asking for me to find you. It looks like it's my lucky day!" They power up their weapons. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_REBEL_ATTACK_3">Your distress beacon must be working because a ship just jumped nearby. You run a scan on it and activate a red alert. It's a Rebel fighter! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>
<text name="text_FUEL_ON_REBEL_ATTACK_4">A Rebel ship jumps in and hails you, "I knew you would slip up some time. Surrender quietly!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 30-30, 80s ]</text>

