<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c2_c3_choice">(Adv. Medbay) Quickly teleport him back to the medbay. [ HScrap, Mantis Crew Gain w/Max Skills, High Scrap & Weapon Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c2_c4_choice">(Adv. Clone Bay) Quickly configure the Clone Bay to save him. [ HScrap, Mantis Crew Gain w/Max Skills, High Scrap & Weapon Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c2_choice">(Teleporter) Quickly teleport additional crew and check for survivors. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c3_c1_choice">Let him die. [ High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c3_c2_choice">Dock and try to speak with him. [ High Standard, High Scrap & Weapon Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c3_c3_choice">(Adv. Medbay) Dock and quickly take him back to the medbay. [ HScrap, Mantis Crew Gain w/Max Skills, High Scrap & Weapon Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_DEFEAT_c3_choice">(Sensors) Quickly scan their ship for survivors. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_c1_choice">(Mantis crewmember) Attempt to hail him. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard + BOs ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_NAMED_THIEF_c2_choice">Prepare to fight. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard + BOs ]</text>
<text name="event_MANTIS_SUN_FIGHT_text">Who knows why the Mantis would venture so close to a sun. Perhaps it makes for more of a challenge? [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Solar-flare ]</text>
<text name="event_START_BEACON_MANTIS_text">You've entered a poorly charted area of space that's known to be home to the Mantis. Ensure your hull plating is up to scratch and that you have enough fuel in the tank to make it through. [ 1-2 Stores, 2-3 Empty, 1-3 Distress, 6-7 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 6-7 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_1">A Mantis military ship appears on local radar alongside the remains of a human freighter. Prepare for a hostile encounter! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_10">The Mantis ship is pleased to see you, and fires up its weapon systems. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_11">You recognize the outline of a Mantis ship against the blackness. Engage! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_12">Something red looms. It's the Mantis. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_13">A Mantis vessel hails you. "This hail is merely a distraction!" You notice their shields and weapons have come online. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_14">You notice a flurry of laser fire glance by the port window. The Mantis are upon you. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_15">The Mantis hail you. Their captain says, "I claim this vessel for my clan. Good hunting!" [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_16">A Mantis female comes on the vidscreen. The females don't make it to authority unless they're particularly vicious. You power the weapons. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_17">A Mantis ship with the markings of a warrior tribe breaks position and attacks! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_18">A Mantis ship hails: "Ah! Fine prey. Fine prey! We honor you with our most eviscerating arsenal!" You sense a cloud to this silver lining and power the weapons. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_19">Children on Earth are told terrible tales of the blood red Mantis invasion ships - much like the one bearing down on you now - which once threatened the planet. You order weapons free! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_2">A Mantis military scout hails your ship. "Foolish alien! Your kind has stifled our greatness for too long! You will rue the day you backed the Federation!" [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_20">A youthful-looking Mantis captain hails. "You, prey, must know. Your death, Kaaazthwak's final kill before maturity. Kaaazthwak pay respects." Seems respects in Mantis culture are paid with lasers. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_3">A small Mantis cruiser is broadcasting a repeating message on a wide-band frequency, "All non-Mantis ships that enter our territory are forfeit. Lower your shields and surrender if you value your lives." [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_4">You detect a small military outpost and a few freighters nearby. This mineral rich planet in an isolated location would be perfect for an illegal Mantis mining operation. As you consider your options, a ship launches from the outpost. Prepare for a fight. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_5">You discover yet another unlicensed and uncharted Mantis colony. They certainly waste no time expanding their claims. A Mantis ship moves to intercept you before you can jump away. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_6">A Mantis military scout seems to have just finished a salvage op on a nearby wreck. They have no time to waste with warnings and appear to wish to fight. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_7">A small military craft hails you and a Mantis captain appears on your receiver. "All local human colonies have been punished for the Federation's transgressions. Submit to processing." [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_8">A nearby Mantis ship begins aggressive maneuvers. You prepare for the worst. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_MANTIS_FIGHT_9">A stream of clicks and gurgling comes on the comm from a hostile Mantis scout. The universal translator might be on the blink, but his intent is obvious. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>

