<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c1_choice">Attack the automated ship to get to the station. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap, Double Reward: [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic | Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | Med. Resources ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c2_choice">Avoid provoking the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c3_choice">(Cloaking) Attempt to stealthily access the space station. [ Double | Auto Ship Fight then Double ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c4_choice">(Improved Cloaking) Use your stealth to access the space station. [ Double ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c5_choice">(Hacking) Try to hack the station to prevent an alert. [ -1 Missle, Double | -1 Missle, Auto Ship Fight then Double ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c6_choice">(Improved Hacking) Hack the station to prevent an alert. [ -1 Missle, Double ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_CLOAK_2_text">You try to sneak past the automated ship but it quickly turns and attacks! [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap, Double Reward: [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic | Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | Med. Resources ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_HACK_2_text">You send a Missle to hack the station but the automated ship notices and turns to attack! [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap, Double Reward: [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic | Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | Med. Resources ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_LOST_SHIP_c1_choice">Attempt to follow and help them. [ Nothing Happens | Crew Gain | Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_LOST_SHIP_c2_choice">Keep your position, they can handle themselves. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_LOST_SHIP_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Lock onto their life-signs with your teleporter. [ Crew Gain, MScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_LOST_SHIP_c4_choice">(Long-ranged Scanner) Pump extra power into your sensors and try to track them. [ Crew Gain | MScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_LOST_SHIP_LIST_2_text">While searching fruitlessly through the nebula, you stumble upon the Rebel ship which the Federation loyalists were likely hiding from. You prepare for a fight. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_MANTIS_CHOICE_c1_choice">There won't be a next time. Open fire! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_MANTIS_CHOICE_c2_choice">This place is dangerous enough. Move on. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c1_choice">Attack the pirate. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Drones | x2 MScrap | x2 Low Standard | High Standard ]; Crew Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Crew Gain, HScrap | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c1_text">You power up your weapons and move in to engage. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Drones | x2 MScrap | x2 Low Standard | High Standard ]; Crew Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Crew Gain, HScrap | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 3-4, 35s ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c2_choice">Ignore the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c3_c1_choice">Take their bribe. [ Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c3_c2_choice">Ignore their bribe and attack. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Drones | x2 MScrap | x2 Low Standard | High Standard ], Crew Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Crew Gain, HScrap | Med. Scrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 3-4, 35s ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_PIRATE_SMUGGLE_c3_choice">(Weapons) Activate your advanced weapons threateningly. [ Med. Scrap & Fuel or attack anyway ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c1_choice">Stay hidden. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c2_choice">Prepare to chase them! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards | Nothing Happens | Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c3_choice">(Advanced Sensors) Try to track them as you move to engage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c4_choice">(Long-ranged Scanner) Try to track them as you move to engage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c5_choice">(Lifeform Scanner) Use their life signatures to follow. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_LIST_1_text">You follow their vapour trails and surf onto their six o'clock, weapons hot. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c3_text">As soon as they see you they make a run for it. You squeeze what you can out of the malfunctioning sensors and are able to keep track of them long enough to get in firing range. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_CHASE_c5_text">Your augment's ability to keep track of their life signatures within the nebula proves useful. You catch up to the ship and prepare for a fight. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_UNDETECTED_c1_choice">Attack the ship. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_UNDETECTED_c2_choice">Attempt to remain concealed. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards (Avoid with Lvl4 Engines) | Nothing Happens | Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_UNDETECTED_c3_choice">(Cloaking) Cloak to stay hidden. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_UNDETECTED_LIST_1_c1_choice">Prepare to fight. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_REBEL_UNDETECTED_LIST_1_c2_choice">(Engines) Fully power the engines to out-run them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ROCK_RACIST_c1_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ROCK_RACIST_c2_choice">Repugnant?! Arm the weapons! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ROCK_RACIST_c3_choice">(Rock crewmember) Offer to lead them out of the nebula. [ High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST_2_c1_choice">Attack the ship! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST_2_c2_choice">Learn a valuable lesson and move on. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_1_c1_choice">Buy the weapon. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_2_text">Once "convinced" to help, he casually states that his offer was actually a lie and that they planned to attack your ship. By the time he returns to his senses you've already prepared your ship to fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c1_choice">Ignore the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c2_choice">Attack the ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c3_choice">Purchase an unknown weapon for 45 scrap. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon | -45 Scrap [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards or Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c4_choice">(Mind Control) Convince him to make it a better deal. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon or Nothing Happens | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c1_choice">Prepare to fight. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c2_choice">(Engines) Attempt to out-run it. [ Nothing Happens | Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c3_choice">(Improved Engines) Attempt to out-run it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c4_choice">(Cloaking) Use your cloaking to escape. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c1_choice">Manually search the wreckage for survivors and equipment. [ -4 Hull, High Resources | Crew Gain, Low Standard | Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), Low Standard | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c2_choice">Avoid the risk and wait to jump away unscathed. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c3_choice">(Piloting) Have your pilot carefully explore the debris. [ Crew Gain, Low Standard | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Low Scrap & Weapon | Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_REBEL_text">You arrive in the middle of a plasma storm. Despite the harsh conditions, a Rebel scout seems to be waiting for you. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Ion-storm; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_1">You cross paths with an advance scout of the Rebel fleet searching this section of the nebula for your ship. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_2">You jump into a calmer part of the nebula. However, your relief fades as a Rebel scout jumps to the beacon and moves in to attack. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_3">The tangled wrecks of many ships wait in dormancy here. You see lights flicker on what looks like debris. A Rebel scout bursts out of the wreckage! [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_4">This Missle isn't looking for you. Perhaps it's scouting ahead for the Rebel expansion or maybe they're seeking to use this nebula for cover. Regardless, it identifies you as hostile. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_5">It's worrying that the Rebels have penetrated so deep into uncharted space, even if it is only an unmanned craft. It arms its weapons; you should do the same. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_1">Nebulas are known to be popular Mantis hunting grounds. Information you would have done well to heed here. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_2">You detect a Mantis expedition vessel returning home with its haul. So determined are they, in fact, that they don't wait to see if you're hostile before firing. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_3">A Mantis ship, lost in the storm, hails you. "Sensors are out. We have no local telemetry. We will take yours." You detect a power increase in their weapons systems. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_4">A Mantis ship hails you through the storm: "These are sacred Urggghtnag clan hunting grounds. You are prey." Shields up! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_5">You notice a Mantis attack ship ducking between the clouds of swirling space  Resources; it's hunting you. You try to get the jump and move in to attack. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_1">As you drift through the nebula an unmarked vessel descends from the clouds and into your wake. Their weapons come online. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_2">A pirate ship pulls out of the ether and hails: "You know what I love about this part of the galaxy? The explorers! You always carry such fine loot." They lock weapons. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_3">As you coast through the nebula a pirate ship matches your course and closes the distance. Better to pick your battleground, but beggars can't be choosers. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_4">A hostile vessel descends from out of the nebula. Combat stations! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_5">You try to read the ID of a ship ahead in the fog, but it's too thick to penetrate. You have your answer when the ship turns, weapons hot! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_1">You cross paths with an advance scout of the Rebel fleet searching this section of the nebula for your ship. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_2">A ship bearing Rebel colors can be seen waiting near the beacon. They must have been waiting for you, since they engage immediately. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_3">The Rebels must have anticipated you would try to lose them within the nebula. A scout is waiting for you at the beacon. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_4">It looks like you will be unable to avoid the Rebels by traveling through the nebula. A Rebel ship is waiting for you near the beacon. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_5">Shortly after you arrive, a Rebel ship jumps nearby. There looks to be no escape. Prepare for a fight! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_6">Newton-knows what brings this Rebel ship so far out; its captain hails, but does a double take when he identifies your ship. They open fire. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_7">A Rebel ship hails, but you don't take chances in conditions like this. You block the frequency and prepare to engage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_1">This nebula must have been an important hub at one point; placing all of these jump beacons would be no easy task. However, now it's hardly navigable. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_2">Nebulas were always dangerous places. Many electronics fail in these clouds. You will have to tread lightly. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_3">You've entered a sector thick with nebulas. You'll have to navigate on instinct. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_4">You've entered a nebula-rich sector. You may put a few light years on the fleet, but that's only useful if you make it out the other side. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_5">Thanks to the high nebula density of this sector very little of it has been charted, and rumours of what lurks in the depths abound. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_6">The gases that make up the nebulas in this sector threaten to impair your systems; but you have to press on. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>

<!-- data/events_pirate.xml -->
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c1_choice">Bring it aboard. [ Med. Standard | LScrap | 2-4 Human Boarders | 2-4 Human Boarders, Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c2_choice">Leave it alone, this looks suspicious. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c3_choice">(Advanced Sensors) Run an advanced scan on the boxes. [ 20-35 Scrap | Med. Standard | [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards or Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c4_choice">(Long-Ranged Scanners) Run an advanced scan on the boxes. [ 20-35 Scrap | Med. Standard | Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards or Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_LIST_4_text">You bring the cargo aboard. Before you have a chance to open it a pirate ship appears out of hiding and charges. At the same time, the crates fly open. Intruders aboard the ship! [ 2-4 Human Boarders, Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0-5, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.3, 2-4, 15s ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_SCAN_LIST_3_c1_choice">Destroy the crates to prevent another ship from falling victim. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_SCAN_LIST_3_c1_text">You fire on the crates, breaking them open and scattering the pirates into empty space. A pirate ship appears out of nowhere with a message, "You will pay for that!" [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0-5, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.3, 2-4, 15s ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_SCAN_LIST_3_c2_choice">Leave it alone and prepare to jump. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c1_choice">Buy one slave and free them to join your crew. [ Crew Gain, -25-45 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c2_choice">Attack the slaver scum. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c3_choice">Ignore the slaver and continue on your way. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c4_choice">(Teleporter) Use your teleporter to attempt to board the ship and release some of the slaves. [ x2 Crew Gain, same as above | Same as above ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_TELEPORTER_1_text">You beam a small team into their holds. They work quickly to free the slaves and teleport back to your ship. One of the captives seems fit for battle and you throw them a weapon in preparation for a fight. [ Crew Gain, Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_TELEPORTER_2_text">You teleport an away team into their hold to attempt to free their prisoners. They are able to get to one person before being caught and forced into a corner by the crew. You quickly beam the team and prisoner back to your ship. [ Crew Gain, Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_TELEPORTER_3_text">You beam a team onto their ship. However, your estimations of the location of their prisoners was off. By the time they get their bearings the slavers spot them. You beam them back to the ship and prepare for a fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_ASTEROID_c1_choice">Turn and fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_c1_choice">Accept their bribe. [ Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_c2_choice">Try to be a hero. Attack the pirate. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: RScrap; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ [ Low Standard or Fleet Delay ] | MScrap | Nothing Happens | Store | +15 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_c2_text">The pirate ship stops its pursuit and locks weapons onto your ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: RScrap; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ [ Low Standard or Fleet Delay ] | MScrap | Nothing Happens | Store | +15 Hull ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 3-4, High Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.4, 3-4, Double ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_WIN_1_c1_choice">Destroy the ship and salvage it. [ Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_WIN_1_c2_choice">Use the leverage you gained by saving their lives to convince them to delay the pursuing fleet. [ Fleet Delay ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CHOICE_c2_choice">Reject their 'offer'. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CHOICE_c2_text">"Too bad... You will regret this decision!" [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_c1_text">You power up your weapons and engage the pirate ship. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_NO_ESCAPE_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Pirate Ship Fight w/Hacking@0, Kill Reward: Random Scrap & Fuel, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_NO_ESCAPE_text">Once you arrive, your screen lights up with warnings. A nearby pirate seems to have advanced hacking tools and they have tried to shut down your engines. Your crew manages to keep them barely operational and you move into attack. [ Pirate Ship Fight w/Engines@1, Kill Reward: Random Scrap & Fuel, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c1_choice">Draw straws and send a crew-member over to the slavers. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c2_choice">We will never surrender one of our crew to slavers! [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c3_choice">(Engines) Attempt to out-run the slaver ship. [ x2 Nothing Happens | Same as above ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_RUN_1_text">You quickly fire up your engines and make a break for it. However, it seems to be in vain. They catch up to you effortlessly and power up their weapons. [ Pirate Ship Fight; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, Med. Standard | Crew Gain, High Standard | High Standard ]; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.2, 2-4, Crew Gain; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SUN_text">This beacon has been placed too close to a super-giant class Med. star! The ship will gradually overheat until you get out of here... or die. A pirate, apparently oblivious to the danger of the sun, moves in to engage. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; S; 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST_1_c1_choice">Welcome aboard! [ Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST_1_c2_choice">Decline their request. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_1">As you jump into the system a pirate advances on your position. They are refusing all hails. Prepare for a fight. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_2">Soon after arriving in the system you are hailed by a small cruiser. "What good fortune that we happen to run into each other. Nothing personal, but you have some information we need!" [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_3">At first it appears you've arrived in an empty system, but a ship appears from behind a planet and hails you: "Haha! I am the dread pirate Tuco, prepare to die!" [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_4">The only other ship at this beacon messages you: "Finally, after months of waiting, someone has fallen into our trap!" [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_5">You barely have time to register jump completion before your ship warns you of an incoming ship with weapons hot. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_1">A few years ago this region was bustling with trade activity. Now it is overrun with bandits and marauders. You should tread lightly here. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_2">This somewhat isolated region was thrown into chaos at the start of the rebellion. Even in peacetime it was always beset by pirates but now it houses a center of operations for countless pirate fleets. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_3">If the reports are true, this area has been under the control of pirates for quite some time. Some traders still attempt to trade with the few settlements that remain, but they do so at great risk. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_4">A few Federation-friendly planets still exist in this sector, but they are constantly under attack by pirate raids. This is a dangerous sector, so be careful. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

<!-- data/events_rebel.xml -->
<text name="event_AUTO_CIVILIAN_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_CIVILIAN_c1_text">You power up your weapons and engage the automated ship. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ Crew Gain | Med. Standard | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | +5 Hull | Nothing Happens ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_CIVILIAN_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c1_choice">Attack the automated ship to get to the storage cache. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap, Double Reward: [ Low Scrap & Missle Schematic | Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | Med. Resources ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c2_choice">Avoid provoking the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c3_choice">(Cloaking) Attempt to cloak and access the cache. [ Straight to Double | Same as above ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c1_choice">Attack the automated ship to get to the sensor station. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Double Reward: Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c2_choice">Avoid provoking the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c3_choice">(Sensors) Use your sensors to attempt to access the data. [ Map | Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: LScrap, Double Reward: Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c4_choice">(Teleporter) Beam directly onto the station to try to avoid detection. [ Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c1_choice">Approach the station. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: MScrap, More... ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c2_choice">Keep your distance and wait for the FTL to charge. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c3_choice">(Combat Missle) Send a Missle to distract the automated ship. [ Drones -1 [ x2 [ Fleet Delay | Map | Nothing Happens | Fleet Advance ] | Same as above ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_HACKER_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_HACKER_text">Your arrival is greeted by numerous computer alerts. The nearby automated Rebel scout has used a local satellite to deploy a virus to disrupt your Shields System. Hopefully it won't cause further problems before you can destroy it. [ Auto Ship Fight w/Shields@Half, Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c1_choice">Attempt to download the ship's data stores. [ Map, Low Standard | Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c2_choice">Don't risk activating it, and just strip the ship for any useful scrap. [ LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c3_choice">(Sensors) Remotely scan the ship. [ Map, Low Standard | More... ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_SENSORS_2_c1_choice">Yes. [ Map, Low Standard | Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_SENSORS_2_c2_choice">No. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_c1_choice">Look around. [ MiniFlagship Ship Fight Kill Reward: 5 Fuel, 5 Missiles, 5 Drones, High Scrap & Weapon, Fleet Delay x2 ]</text>
<text name="event_FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_c1_text">Warning lights flash as scans identify the gigantic ship under construction - it's a second Rebel Flagship! This must be the secret shipyards where the first one was built, and you've accidentally stumbled across it! Even in its weakened state, the Rebel ship powers up... get ready, you've got a hell of a fight on your hands. [ MiniFlagship Ship Fight Kill Reward: 5 Fuel, 5 Missiles, 5 Drones, High Scrap & Weapon, Fleet Delay x2 ]</text>
<text name="event_FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_c2_choice">Leave immediately. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_TRANSPORT_c1_choice">Demand the surrender of their goods. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Drones | x2 Med. ScrapOnly | x2 Low Standard | High Standard ]; Crew Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Crew Gain, HScrap | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ] ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_TRANSPORT_c1_text">You prepare to secure their cargo by force. [ Rebel Ship Fight Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 14-14, 40s; Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Low Standard | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic | Med. Scrap & Drones | x2 Med. ScrapOnly | x2 Low Standard | High Standard ]; Crew Kill Reward: [ Med. Scrap & Weapon | Crew Gain, HScrap | MScrap | Med. Scrap & Missle Schematic ] ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_TRANSPORT_c2_choice">Avoid the ship. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_REFUEL_STATION_c1_choice">Intervene to defend the outpost. [ Auto Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Double Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_REFUEL_STATION_c2_choice">Avoid the conflict. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SQUAT_REFUEL_STATION_c1_choice">Intervene to defend the outpost. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_SQUAT_REFUEL_STATION_c1_text">The rebel responds to your threat, "I don't know who you are, but no one defies the Rebel Fleet!" They move in to engage. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Double Reward: Med. Scrap & Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_SQUAT_REFUEL_STATION_c2_choice">Avoid the conflict. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_HELPERS_SHIP_destroyed_c1_choice">Steal the civilian supplies. [ Low Scrap & Drones | Nothing Happens | LScrap | -2 Hull ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_HELPERS_SHIP_destroyed_c2_choice">Leave the civilians alone. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_1">You receive a message from a nearby Rebel station, "You have a lot of guts passing through our space, I'll give you that." He turns giving an order, "Kill their crew, I want that ship intact." [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; 2-3 Human Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_2">Your sensors warn of an incoming Rebel ship at the same time as you hear the telltale signs of a teleporter. You hear someone taunt from within the ship, "Ready to die? I sure am ready to get a promotion!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; 2-3 Human Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_3">Incoming message, "Hello Captain," says a Rebel in an officer's garb. "How very generous of you to turn yourself in. Prepare to be boarded. Come quietly and we may be lenient." [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; 2-3 Human Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_4">You receive a message on a low-band channel. "You're surrounded, just like the last of your Federation friends. Just die already." The enemy has teleported onto your ship! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; 2-3 Human Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_1">Your ship is hailed. "We've found you at last. Prepare to die!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_10">A Rebel ship is guarding this beacon. You order a pursuit course and prepare to scratch up one more. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_2">A small Rebel ship is docked at a small station. You try to lay low but it spots you. Power up the weapons! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_3">A Rebel ship has been patrolling this region. As soon as you arrive it begins its assault. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_4">A Rebel ship hails you: "Federation scum! We've waited a long time for this!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_5">You receive a transmission: "Sorry sir, this is nothing personal but we're under orders." The Rebel ship's weapons go hot. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_6">By the time you notice the Rebel ship behind the beacon, it's too late to avoid a fight. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_7">A Rebel ship hails. "We did not fight a war to let a single Federation ship shatter our dreams of a better galaxy!" He locks weapons. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_8">A Rebel ship approaches cautiously. "Personally," says the captain, "I'd have stuck with the Federation. But I'Med. a soldier, sir, and I'Med. no use without a war to fight. Raise your shields!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_9">You're hailed by a Rebel ship: "When the rebellion is complete you'll see the safer world we provide. Well, you won't, but you get the point." They arm weapons. [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): [ 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources ], Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_1">You discover one of the Rebel's autonomous scouts. The ship's AI wastes no time in engaging your ship. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_2">Your ship is hailed: "This is an automated message. Resisting our takeover is pointless. Prepare to die." It appears this Rebel ship is run by an AI. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_3">A Rebel autonomous scout is exploring this beacon. You attempt to hide behind a nearby moon, but the ship finds you and begins its assault. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_4">The AI of a nearby small Rebel scout immediately identifies you as a threat and engages. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_5">A Rebel ship moves in to engage. You attempt to open communications, but realize the futility of that action when you see the ship is run by an AI. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_6">This must be one of the Rebels' unmanned scout ships. Looks like there's no way around a fight. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_7">Another unmanned ship patrols this area. You prepare the ship for combat. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_8">This beacon is being patrolled by a unmanned scout. A fight is unavoidable. [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_9">A small shuttle appears on the local radar. Turns out it is a Rebel automated scout! [ Auto Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_1">This sector was bustling with activity just a few years ago. Now, more than half of the jump beacons have been destroyed, many settlements have been abandoned and the Rebels patrol constantly. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_2">This sector was hit hard by the rebellion. The many alien settlements and stations located here are now watched over by almost an equal number of Rebel bases, heavy-handedly 'keeping the peace'. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_3">Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_4">At one point this was one of the most commonly traveled sectors. Knowing that, the Rebels have stationed a number of fleets here. Be careful. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_5">You will have to be very cautious in this sector. The Rebels have full control and are no doubt looking for you. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

<!-- data/events_rock.xml -->
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c1_choice">Tell them their god sent them here to join your crew. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c2_choice">Promise to share with them the truths they've been denied. [ Rock Crew Gain | x2 Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c3_choice">(Improved Sensors) Show them to your data suite. [ Rock Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c1_choice">Strip the ship. [ Low Standard | Low Standard, Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ x2 Nothing Happens | Low Standard, Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Check for lifeforms and keep a lookout for ships while looting the wreck. [ Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_LEAVE_3_text">Before you have a chance to leave, a Rock patrol ship arrives and you intercept their comm chatter, "...appears we've finally found them. Their killing spree ends now!" Before you can plead your innocence they move in to attack. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_STRIP_2_text">A Rock patrol ship jumps in while you are salvaging the ship. They message you, "Filthy pirates! Prepare to die!" You doubt explaining your mission will convince them of your need. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c1_choice">Wait, then attack the surviving Mantis. [ Mantis Ship Fight w/Enemy Weapons@2, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard | Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c3_choice">(Repair Missle) Repair the Rock ship. [ High Standard, -1 Missle ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c4_choice">(Hull Repair Missle) Repair their hull. [ -1 Missle, Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward:Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_LIST_1_text">The Mantis craft are both too busy slaughtering one another to notice you. Eventually the smaller ship gets the upper hand, but they must have blown a fuse in the assault and their weapons system is inoperable. Now is the time to attack! [ Mantis Ship Fight w/Enemy weapons@2 Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_LIST_2_text">The Mantis craft may have their differences, but when it comes to you they are of one mind. The smaller ship suffers a power failure as it moves to engage, but the larger one lets off a volley of fire and moves in to attack! [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c1_choice">Attack! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c1_text">No species deserves a Mantis hunter on their back - time to make the galaxy a little safer. Engage! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c3_choice">(Rock Ship) Ram the bastards. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards, Enemy engines@0 ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c3_text">Before they have a chance, you ram your ship into theirs, causing irreparable damage to their engines. Luckily, your ship's armored hull is hardly dented from the impact. The Mantis ship careens away and you move in to attack. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards, Enemy engines@0 ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c4_choice">(Rock Crew) Put your Rock crewmember on the comm. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c4_text">The two aliens face one another over the vidscreen. "Cave-dwelling pebble-man!" yells the furious Mantis captain. "See, I paint my ship with your companions! I paint my ship with you!" [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_START_c1_choice">Accept the passenger. [ Rock Marriage Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_START_c1_text">"You surprise me, off-worlder. Thank you. The passenger will be with you momentarily." She refuses to enter the main hold and prefers to wait in the cargo bay. [ Rock Marriage Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_START_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_c1_c1_choice">Hand her over. [ Random Augment, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_c1_c2_choice">Refuse to comply. [ +1 Rock Crew, Rock Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_SHIP_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Accept their offer. [ Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c1_choice">Send someone out there to defuse it. [ MScrap | [ MScrap | -6 Hull, Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c2_choice">(Missile Weapon) Attempt a controlled detonation using a missile. [ -4 Hull, -1 Missle, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c3_choice">(Beam Missle) Use a Missle to cut away the mine with a precision beam. [ -1 Missle, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c2_choice">(Improved Engines) Reverse thrusters! [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_DEFUSE_2_c1_choice">Red! [ MScrap | -6 Hull, Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_DEFUSE_2_c2_choice">Blue! [ MScrap | -6 Hull, Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive) ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c1_choice">"We're going to save them or die trying." [ Rock Homeworld Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c2_choice">"We're strong enough to destroy you!" [ Rock Homeworld Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c3_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK2_text">You arrive at the coordinates given and find yourself dangerously close to an Med.-class star! The other ship messages you, "Let's see how long your puny ship can handle this heat! Prepare for a challenge!" [ Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 28-28, 32s, Quest [ Rock Plating , +29 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_ATHIEST_BAD_1">They barely hear out your appeals before yelling, "These are the lies I sought to escape!" Looks like they're charging weapons! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_ATHIEST_BAD_2">They listen to your appeals and whisper, "Traitors to truth. You're no better than them!" Chaos ensues. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_1">You arrive in an asteroid field and immediately begin evasive maneuvers when a loud clunk reverberates through the ship. At first you think the hull has been hit, but the noise came from some Rock intruders teleporting aboard the ship! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids, 1-2 Rock Boarders, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_2">Your shields are being taxed as they deflect the debris from an asteroid field. As you weave your way between the rocks, you happen upon a Rock pirate stronghold. You register teleport signatures and hear shouts aboard the ship. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids, 1-2 Rock Boarders, Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_SHIP_1">You passively scan a small Rock station that is next to the beacon. However they must not have appreciated your curiosity. A Rock ship pulls away from the station and you register an incoming teleporter signal as well! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards, 1-3 Rock Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_SHIP_2">You find a Rock ship docked with a damaged Mantis fighter. Before you have a chance to hail them, the ship moves in to attack you and you register teleporter symbols from the disabled ship. They're using Mantis tech to board you! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards, 1-3 Rock Boarders; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_1">A Rock mining vessel is harvesting the mineral-rich asteroids in this locality, and their scouts take your presence to be a transgression. Battle stations! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_2">A rookie Rock cargo ship has taken its orders too literally and took the most direct route to their destination... right through an asteroid field. They're confused and fire wildly as you jump in. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_3">The captain of a Rock freighter lost in the asteroid field hails you: "Our co-ordinates led us here, but only death greets us. What must be must be. Death to all." You power up the battle systems and wonder how long they've been stuck here. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_ASTEROID_1">Minute fissures in the shields spark and crackle as the ship jumps into the wake of a huge asteroid. More asteroids follow, as does a lost and aggressive Rock pirate ship. [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_ASTEROID_2">You exit the jump surrounded by dirt and rocks. Before long a blast is deflected by your shield, but that was no asteroid... Incoming pirate! [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_SUN_1">Unusual solar activity in this region means you need to get out, quick. The Rock pirate nearby apparently thinks otherwise as they move to attack your ship. [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Solar-flare ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_SUN_2">A Rock ship is silhouetted against a sun in supernova. They hail: "Even out here you follow us! We only wish to be left alone!" Out of panic or anger, they charge their weapons. [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Solar-flare ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_1">As a naturally warlike species with few inter-galactic diplomatic ties, the Rock people have garnered quite a reputation as fearsome pirates. You stumble across one of their ships and they promptly live up to type. [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_2">A Rock ship flies past your windows and you recognize outcast decorations on the hull. These must be pirates! [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_3">A motley collection of Rock ships are stationed around this beacon - they look to have resorted to a pirate's life. Defensive maneuvers! [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_4">As a naturally warlike species with few intergalactic diplomatic ties, the Rock people have garnered quite a reputation as fearsome pirates. You stumble across one of their ships and they promptly live up to type. [ Pirate Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_1">You encounter a Rock vessel and attempt to open trading frequencies, but they take it as an act of cultural transgression and open fire. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_2">You jump into the middle of a Rock excavation project on a nearby moon. Unimpressed with your intrusion they move to defend themselves! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_3">You intercept chatter from an approaching Rock ship: "Weapons, moving in to engage, arm the tubes." There is no talking to these guys. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_4">As you jump in, a vast figure appears on the view-screen. The Rock captain rubs the green, moss-like appendage on his chin and then orders his crew to open fire. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_5">It looks quiet, but you realize your computer is being scanned. A hidden Rock vessel hails you: "Why do you fill your computer with lies?! These are not the holy words!" Before you can interject they open fire. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_6">You notice a Rock ship performing combat exercises. However, they quickly change their course to engage your ship. They apparently treat unregistered alien ships as handy target practice. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_7">A loud 'thud' resounds through the ship after jump completion - you've just shunted a Rock fighter and he's already preparing to fire! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_8">You're intercepted by a Rock salvage operation. They don't seem to mind that you're still on board while they junk your ship. [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ROCK_1">The Rock people have a particularly aggressive stance toward alien races trespassing in their space. You should tread carefully here. [ 2 Stores, 2-3 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 7-8 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ROCK_2">The Rock people are a powerful and proud race. It is not unheard of to have a peaceful journey through their lands, but don't count on it. [ 2 Stores, 2-3 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 7-8 Neutral ]</text>

<!-- data/events_ships.xml -->
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_CONVOY_surrender_c1_choice">Stop the fight. [ Low Scrap & Fuel, +8 Hull ]</text>
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_CONVOY_surrender_c2_choice">Finish them off. [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_HUNTER_surrender_c1_choice">Accept their surrender. [ HumanCrew Gain ]</text>
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_HUNTER_surrender_c2_choice">Finish them off. [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_SHIP_surrender_c1_choice">Accept their surrender. [ x2 Nothing Happens | x4 Random Resources | Random Resources or Crystal Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="ship_CRYSTAL_SHIP_surrender_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Kill Reward: Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="ship_PIRATE_BRIBER_surrender_c1_choice">Accept the more generous bribe and leave. [ High Resources ]</text>
<text name="ship_PIRATE_BRIBER_surrender_c2_choice">Reject the offer and continue your assault. [ Kill Reward: RScrap, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ [ Low Standard or Fleet Delay ] | MScrap | Nothing Happens | Store | +15 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="ship_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP1_surrender_c1_choice">Continue fighting the pirate. [ Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP1_surrender_c2_choice">Let the pirate escape and go after the Slugman ship. [ HScrap ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_AUTO_RADAR_destroyed_c1_choice">Attempt to manually hack into the station. [ Fleet Delay | Map | Nothing Happens | Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_AUTO_RADAR_destroyed_c2_choice">Don't risk it. Leave the station. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_AUTO_RADAR_destroyed_c3_choice">(Hacking) Use a Missle to hack into the station. [ Fleet Delay, -1 Missle, Map ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_AUTO_WARNING_escape_text">The ship starts to power up its FTL Drive. If it gets away, it will no doubt warn the fleet of your position! [ Auto Ship Fight; Kill Reward: Low Standard; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 22-22, 40s, Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_ENGI_UNLOCK_2FAKE_escape_text">As soon as they see you, they power up their engines to jump away. Stop them! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard (Decoy), High Standard (Real); Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 18-18, 40s; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 4-4, Engi Unlock Quest (Real) or Nothing (Decoy) ]</text>
<text name="ship_REBEL_ENGI_UNLOCK_2REAL_escape_text">As soon as they see you they power up their engines to jump away. Stop them! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard (Decoy), High Standard (Real); Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 18-18, 40s; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 4-4, Engi Unlock Quest (Real) or Nothing (Decoy) ]</text>
<text name="ship_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_destroyed_c1_choice">Leave them be. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="ship_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_destroyed_c2_choice">Finish them off. [ Low Scrap & Augment | Random Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_SQUAT_PIRATE_MERCENARY_surrender_c1_choice">Let them live and then return to the settlement. [ Med. Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="ship_SQUAT_PIRATE_MERCENARY_surrender_c2_choice">Forget your promise, they die! [ Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Low Standard ]</text>
<text name="ship_SQUAT_WARNING_escape_text">They are powering up their FTL! If they get away, they will no doubt warn the fleet of your position! [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 22-22, 40s, Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="ship_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_destroyed_c1_c1_choice">Let him go. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="ship_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_destroyed_c1_c2_choice">Offer to hire him for 40 scrap. [ Nothing Happens | 40 Scrap for Zoltan Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="ship_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_surrender_text">The Zoltan captain sends an urgent hail: "Wait, this was all a test! A test that you passed! A diverse crew, working together, surely a sight to warm the heart of any dispassionate observer. Come, I shall join your crew!" [ Low Standard, Zoltan Crew Gain ]</text>

