<text name="event_NEBULA_BATTLEFIELD_c2_choice">Investigate the battlefield. [ -5 Hull | x3 Nothing Happens | [ Abadoth Quest or BOs for Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c1_choice">Shields. [ Slug Ship Fight Shields@half Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c2_choice">Oxygen. [ Slug Ship Fight Oxygen@half Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c3_choice">Weapons. [ Slug Ship Fight Weapons@half Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c4_choice">Offer 35 scrap to leave you alone. [ -35 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c5_choice">(Hacking System) Counter any hack attempt. [ Slug Ship Fight Hacking@0 Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_DOORS_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slug Ship Fight Hacking@0, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_DOORS_text">There are few more vicious beasts in the galaxy than a Slug with his back to the wall. The faltering ship armed with fire-weapons uses a remote hacking tool to try and disable your door system - they're going to burn you out! [ Slug Ship Fight Doors@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c1_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c1_choice">Understood. [ [ +5 Fuel, Store | Slug Ship Fight 1 Boarder, Weapons@0, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard | 2 Boarders, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ] or [ Nothing | 1 Boarder, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c1_c2_choice">Forget this. [ Nothing Happens | 1 Boarder, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c3_choice">(Slug crewmember) Our Slug senses someone aboard the ship. Investigate it. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c3_text">It looks like the merchant was trying to stall you while someone teleported on board. You catch him before he could finish and he teleports away. You immediately prepare for battle. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_choice">Ask to see the goods. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_LIST_2_text">"During our discussion, my man hass taken the liberty of disabling your weaponss to prevent any complications while completing our... transssaction..." You suddenly register multiple weapon locks, but your own weapons are not responding. Get out of there! [ Slug Ship Fight, 1 Slug Boarder, Weapons@0, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_LIST_3_text">"Thank you. If you could do me one more courtesssy... please die quietly." You suddenly hear gunshots aboard the ship. He must have been stalling for time while they boarded your ship! [ 1 Slug Boarder, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c1_choice">No thanks. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c2_choice">Sure. [ Various Bad Things ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c3_choice">Ask if they would like payment. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 | Nothing Happens or +10 Hull for 50 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_1_c1_choice">Accept. [ -50 Scrap, +10 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_2_text">Just before the transmission is cut you hear, "They're not falling for it. Just kill the crew and we can ssstrip..." Looks like you're not getting out of here without a fight. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT1_3_text">As you dock with the station your readings go haywire. An EMP blast resonates throughout the ship and your engines shut down. You're a sitting duck as a ship reveals itself and silently moves in to attack! [ Slug Ship Fight w/Engines@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_1_c1_choice">Give them the 15 fuel they demand. [ -15 Fuel ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_1_c2_choice">That's ridiculous! [ -5 Hull, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_1_c2_text">"I'Med. ssssorry to hear that." He presses a button and an explosion rocks the ship. They must have planted a bomb while 'repairing'! Prepare for a fight! [ -5 Hull, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_2_c1_choice">Give them the 50 scrap they demand. [ -50 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_2_c2_choice">Let's get out of here! [ Slug Ship Fight w/Weapons@half; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_RESULT2_2_c2_text">You activate your thrusters and force your way away from the station. A ship quickly moves in to engage. You'll need to get out of here fast; there may not be time to get the weapons fully operational! [ Slug Ship Fight w/Weapons@half; Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MANTIS_text">The Mantis attack ship here looks to have been hunting Slugs on their home turf - a rare test of honor for the mightiest Mantis crews. Weapons up! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_c2_choice">(Improved Medbay) Try to squeeze some extra power to the system. [ Slug Ship Fight Medbay@half, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slug Ship Fight Hacking@0, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_text">A Slug ship hails you: "We've detected some worrying radiation coming from your medical unit, perhaps you should take a look?" As he signs off, your system shuts off and their crew teleports aboard from a nearby station. They don't look like engineers. [ Slug Ship Fight Clone/Medbay@0, Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_c2_choice">(Improved Oxygen) Try to squeeze some extra power to the system. [ Slug Ship Fight Oxygen@half, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slug Ship Fight Hacking@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_text">The Slugs here use a tactic you hoped you'd never see: they use a remote hacking satellite to sabotage your oxygen production system and then charge fire-weapons - you're going to suffocate! [ Slug Ship Fight Oxygen@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_PIRATE_c1_choice">Attack! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_PIRATE_c2_choice">Keep your distance and hope they haven't seen you yet. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP_c1_choice">Tap their comm frequency. [ Slug Pirate Trap Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP2_c1_c1_choice">Engage the pirate. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer):HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP2_c1_c2_choice">Head for the cache. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_c1_choice">(Slug Crew) Ask your Slug crewmember to scan for life forms. [ Med. Standard or Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_c2_choice">Do a full system scan - though you're sure to lose some of your lead with the Rebels. [ Fleet Advance, Med. Standard or Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_CONCLUSION_c1_choice">Explain about finding the dead crewman. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_CONCLUSION_c2_choice">(Engi Crew) Say ABADOTH. [ Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_CONCLUSION_c3_choice">Say ANODYNE. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_CONCLUSION_c4_choice">Say ABADOTH. [ Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_CONCLUSION_c5_choice">Say ABATODH. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c1_choice">Attack the Mantis ship. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Double Reward: [ Low Scrap & Augment | Random Standard ] ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c2_choice">Attack the Slug ship. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c3_choice">Of all the species in the galaxy, these two deserve one another. You power up the jump drive. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c1_choice">Swear allegiance. [ Nothing Happens | Slug Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c2_choice">Never! [ Slug Ship Fight w/Engines@1, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c3_choice">(Improved Piloting) Override his control. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c4_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slug Ship Fight Hacking@0, Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_c1_choice">Hire Slocknog. [ -55 Scrap, Slug Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_c2_choice">Ignore Slocknog. [ Slug Crew Gain or Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_LIST_1_c1_choice">Rescue him. [ Slug Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_LIST_1_c2_choice">Leave him. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_ROCK_c1_choice">Engage the Slug ship. [ Nothing Happens | Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: [ x2 Nothing Happens | Med. Standard ] ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_ROCK_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ x2 Nothing Happens | Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_ROCK_AVOID_3_text">After the Slugs board the ship, you are surprised to see the Rock ship spring to life and decimate the other ship. They message you, "Pathetic. You are either a coward or an ally of the Slugs. Either way, you don't deserve to live." [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c1_choice">Send some crew to help. [ 1-3 Borders, Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards | Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards | HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c3_choice">(Mantis Crew) Have your Mantis oversee the repairs. [ HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_LIST_1_text">As soon as you board their ship their hostile intentions become clear. Despite being outnumbered, your crew is able to break free of the Slug trap and fight back to the airlock. You pull away from the enemy ship but not before a few Slugs make it on board. [ 1-3 Slug Boarders, SLug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_LIST_2_text">As soon as you board their ship their hostile intentions become clear. On your way back to the airlock, one of your crewmembers is taken out by a well aimed Slug blaster shot. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Revive), Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c1_choice">Drink. [ +10 Hull, Store | -25-35 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c3_choice">(Rock Crew) Have your Rockman pose as captain. [ Store, +10 Hull | Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c2_text">The Slug feigns offense at your refusal, but you sense that he respects your caution. This does not, however, prevent him from returning to his ship and opening fire. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_ROCK_2_text">Your crewmember is able to identify a heavy anaesthetic contained in the flask when he feels slightly drowsy (the Rock digestion system is very robust). His ruse discovered, the Slug immediately returns to his ship and opens fire. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_FIGHT_text">It's rare for the Slugs to stay exposed in open space for long periods - the ship here may be lost, or just passing through, but either way he moves in to attack! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_MANTIS_text">You intercept comm chatter from an incoming Mantis ship. "Look. This ship appears not to be owned by the squishy ones. Maybe they won't smell so bad when we cut them open." They move in on your position. [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Let them live. [ [ HFuel | Low Resources | Med. Resources ] | [ BioBeam or Slug Unlock Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_SURRENDER_c1_c1_choice">Accept the prototype weapon. [ BioBeam ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_SURRENDER_c1_c2_choice">We don't want the weapon, we want information. [ Slug Unlock Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_1_c1_choice">Charge them before they escape. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_1_c2_choice">Try to tail them without being noticed. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard or Nothing Happens or Slug Crew/Lvl2 Sensors BOs ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_2_c1_choice">Fly slowly toward their last known position. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_2_c2_choice">Wait and hope the escort leaves. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_2_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Have your crewmember monitor their life signatures. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 22-22, 35s ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_2_c3_c1_text">The only ship left near the cruiser is an interceptor. This should be easy! [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 22-22, 35s ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_2_c4_choice">(Improved Sensors) Try to maintain a lock on their ships from a distance. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Crew Kill Reward: High Standard, Slug Gel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 22-22, 35s ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Let them live. [ [ HFuel | Low Resources | Med. Resources ] | [ BioBeam or Slug Unlock Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_1">Your sensors are no match for the Slug's telepathic abilities - a ship you never even saw opens fire from astern! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_2">The Slug vessel you encounter here has obviously made a big score and is looking to test its new armaments. They picked the wrong ship to attack. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_3">A Slug passenger ship hails: "Please, your worthy alien highnessesss, we are unarmed and sseeking asssylum." You approach cautiously, and weapons immediately spring from their hull! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_4">A Slug ship - a rogue, you suspect - approaches, but when he sees you're Federation he thinks better of the sneak attack and fires everything he has. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_5">Direct attacks are not preferred by the Slugs, but of the three you see at this beacon, one has the brass to make a move on your position! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_1">There appears to be a pirate ship nearby. Be on your guard; anyone trying to hunt in Slug territory is either formidable or deeply stupid, and in space, either can be dangerous. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_2">"We knew anyone foolish enough to try and sneak through a Slug nebula would stick to open space. Yield your goods and we may let you live." You cut the transmission in lieu of a response. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_3">Before you can take a moment's rest from the ever present nebulas in this sector, a pirate ship appears behind you and opens fire. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_1">As you arrive at the beacon, a hostile ship immediately registers on your scanners. You didn't expect to see Rebels extending their reach into Slug territory. Charge the weapons! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_2">You jump into empty space and are relieved to see your sensors blink back to life. However, you are less pleased to see them immediately register a rebel ship on an approach vector! [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_3">You receive a message from a nearby ship, "Looks like our intelligence was correct! Sneaking through the clouds with the Slugs... No one can hide from the rebellion!" [ Rebel Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 2-3, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_1">The only thing that can render a nebula more dangerous is if it's also home to the Slugs. This particular nebula is just that. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_2">This nebula is home to the telepathic Slugs. They'd sell their own slime for a crate of scrap, but they much prefer to just take it. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_3">You're told the Slug home world is somewhere in this nebula. You can't see them, but you know they're watching. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_4">The Slugs that live in this nebula field are a leisure-centered civilization. Everything in Slug life is done in the pursuit of more currency and more time in which to spend it on extravagant ventures. This, inevitably, leads to much treachery in open space. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_5">The Slugs developed on an ocean planet where the ability to telepathically sense another organism was more important than sight. Today they use this ability to navigate unfettered the depths of the nebulas they inhabit. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_1">The ion storm here threatens to deactivate your core systems, a fact made all the worse for the largely unaffected Slug ships circling like space-vultures. [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Ion-storm; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_2">The Slug ship that descends into view as you enter the ion storm must have sensed your distress - defensive action! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Ion-storm; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_3">You arrive in the middle of an ion storm. Slugs generally avoid these storms but you find one waiting in ambush. Prepare for a fight! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Ion-storm; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_4">You find yourself stuck in the middle of an ion storm with a Slug ship just a short distance away, refusing all hails. You cautiously try to slip further into the clouds, but they turn suddenly to attack! [ Slug Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Ion-storm; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>

<!-- data/events_zoltan.xml -->
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_EYE_c1_choice">Pull the ship in closer. [ Heal Bomb | Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards | HScrap | Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_EYE_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_ROCK_text">This nebula turns out to be the hiding place of a terrified rock crew taking refuge from the Zoltan border police. They don't seem prepared to risk your leaving with their co-ordinates, and open fire! [ Rock Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.7, 3-4, Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c1_choice">Secure the fuel supply. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Scrap & Fuel; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Fuel; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c2_choice">Secure the ammunition. [ Pirate Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Scrap & Missles; Crew Kill Reward: High Scrap & Missles; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c3_choice">Let them leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ASTEROID_text">You arrive in an asteroid field and are greeted by a Zoltan guard, "By attempting to access these closed mining fields, you are in violation of the Natural Mineral Protection Act. Your weaponry will be confiscated for processing." You don't have time for this. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards w/Asteroids ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_BOARDERS_text">There are few more zealous in their customs checks than the Zoltan. A team of border police beam on board. There's just a little confusion over your weapons licences, but things escalate rapidly from heated discussion to gunfire! [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards 3-4 Zoltan Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_BOARDERS_MANTIS_text">The Mantis outcasts sometimes make the mistake of taking the Zoltan for easy game. A scout moves in to attack while a boarding party beams aboard from a nearby transport! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards 2-3 Mantis Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c1_choice">You don't have time for this nonsense. Attack! [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c1_text">Expecting resistance, their Energy Shield is raised and ready for combat. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c2_choice">Submit to profiling. [ Nothing Happens | [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) or [ Zoltan Ship Fight 2-4 Zoltan Boarders, Weapons@half, Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Have your Slug talk them into letting you go. [ MFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c4_choice">(Mind Control) Make the guards believe they have already checked your crew today. [ MFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_LIST_2_c1_choice">Give up your crewmember. [ Crew Loss (Clone Bay Loss) ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_LIST_2_c2_choice">Refuse and fight. [ Zoltan Ship Fight 2-4 Zoltan Boarders, Weapons@half, Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_LIST_2_c2_text">You're not going to leave anyone behind. You pull away from the station with the enemy guards on board. Unfortunately, they are able to sabotage your weapon system in the chaos. It's time to leave! [ Zoltan Ship Fight 2-4 Zoltan Boarders, Weapons@half, Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c1_choice">Interfere and save the Mantis ship. [ Zoltan Ship Fight w/Asteroids Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c1_text">Sometimes you have to bet on the underdog - even on the rare occasions that the underdog is a Mantis warship. You set off for the heart of the asteroid field and engage the Zoltan there. [ Zoltan Ship Fight w/Asteroids Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c2_choice">Interfere and help the Zoltan ship. [ Mantis Ship Fight w/Asteroids Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c2_text">You overtake the Zoltan and catch up with the Mantis ship in the asteroid belt. Time to make some friends. [ Mantis Ship Fight w/Asteroids Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c3_choice">Don't interfere. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ENGI_text">You jump into a debris field that used to be a Zoltan cruiser. Unfortunately, its Engi escort takes you for the attacker and retaliates! They refuse all hails. [ Engi Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_c1_choice">Engage the pirates. [ Pirate Zoltan Ship Fight Kill Reward: [ Med. Standard, Trade -40 Scrap for Zoltan Crew ] Crew Kill Reward: [ High Scrap & Augment ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_MANTIS_text">You pick up the last broadcast from a rupturing Zoltan freighter: "The Mantis, they're here, please-" You're interrupted by fire off the port bow! [ Mantis Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c1_choice">Check it out. [ Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap | -1 Mis [ RScrap | Nothing Happens | Random Scrap & Weapon ] or Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c2_choice">Leave it be. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c3_choice">(Boarding Missle) Send a Missle to probe the surface. [ -1 Missle, Zoltan Crew Gain ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_CHECK_4_c1_choice">Attempt to detonate some explosives to break through the surface. [ -1 Missile, [ Nothing Happens | Low Scrap & Weapon | MScrap ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_CHECK_4_c2_choice">Explosives are too valuable to waste on excavation work. Let's get out of here. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c1_choice">Interfere - make first contact with the primitive aliens. [ Zoltan Ship Fight; Kill Reward: Low Standard, Fleet Advance; Crew Kill Reward: Random Standard, Fleet Advance ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c2_choice">Protect the aliens' way of life - Attack the Rebel ship. [ Rebel Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Scrap & Weapon, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Scrap & Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c3_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c1_choice">Mantis. [ Mantis Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c2_choice">Slug. [ Slug Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c3_choice">Rockmen. [ Rock Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard, Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard, Double Reward: High Standard ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_c1_choice">Dock with them. [ Med. Resources | Zoltan Ship Fight; Kill Reward: Low Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer):[ Low Standard, Zoltan Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_c2_choice">Have them keep their distance. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_LIST_1_text">You allow them to approach, but are caught unaware when they open fire! [ Zoltan Ship Fight Kill Reward: Low Standard; Crew Kill Reward: Med. Standard; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, [ Low Standard, Zoltan Crew Gain ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Accept their offer. [ Random Resources ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c1_choice">Try to talk your way in. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards, 2-4 Zoltan Boarders | [ Store | Primitives Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c2_choice">(Teleporter) Beam directly to the civilian deck. [ Store | Primitives Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c3_choice">(Zoltan Crew) Present his official documentation and pay the entry fee. [ -10 Scrap, [ Store | Primitives Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c4_choice">Leave. [ Nothing Happens ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_1">A Zoltan ship makes contact. "The nature of the day is rotational. The fever is emaciated. The reason is-" They've caught some nasty deep space dementia. Before you can consider finding help for them, they open fire. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_2">You're surprised when a stationary Zoltan ship opens fire. It appears there are aggressive pugilists even among the 'enlightened'. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_3">You receive a message, "This area is off limits. Submit your ship to processing." It's only one guard ship in a lonely beacon. You decide to fight your way out. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_4">You discover a number of Zoltan civilian ships fighting off pirates. Unfortunately one ship mistakes your purpose and moves in to attack! They are refusing all communication; you have no choice but to fight. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_5">Like many areas in Zoltan space, the residents of this sector prepared well for Galactic war. The military here seem to have given up reasoning with foreigners, preferring instead to attack on sight! [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_6">A Zoltan ship is waiting at this beacon. They request your identification, but radiation from the sun in this system is disrupting your communications. They take your silence for aggression and move in to attack. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_7">The Zoltan ship patrolling this area hails you: "This area is off limits. Secrecy is vital." They power their weapons. [ Zoltan Ship Fight Default Rewards ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_1">"Emergency, all ships in range, we are under attack!" The frequency matches a nearby Zoltan ship; you move in on their pursuer. They take your intervention as a cue to jump away. Cowards. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_2">You jump just in time to witness a Zoltan ship's FTL drive overload. In his final moments their captain implores you not to get involved, but it's too late - their attacker is already upon you! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_3">Despite their precautions, pirates have begun to harass the local Zoltan settlements across this sector. One such pirate spots your ship and moves in to attack. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_4">A ship with pirate markings demands your surrender. These are sad times when even Zoltan space is beset by pirates. You doubt these fools will be missed. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_5">You spot a pirate ship looting a small Zoltan cruiser. They spot you and move in to attack before your FTL drive has a chance to recharge. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_6">You jump just in time to witness a Zoltan ship's FTL drive overload. In their final moments they implore you not to get involved, but it's too late - their attacker is already upon you! [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_7">A ship with pirate markings demand that you surrender. These are sad times when even Zoltan space is beset by pirates. You doubt these fools will be missed. [ Pirate Ship Fight Default Rewards; Surrender (Chance, Min-Max, Offer): 0.5, 3-4, Random Resources; Escape (Chance, Min-Max, Timer): 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_1">You've entered Zoltan territory. This species is not renowned for giving anything for nothing, but you can always be assured a fair hearing. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_2">The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_3">You arrive in Zoltan space. From what you have heard they anticipated the coming war and made preparations to hold their borders. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_4">You're far from Federation home space here in Zoltan territory, and it's not clear whether the authorities will have any goodwill remaining. Still, you have to push forward. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

